concept_definition: the existence of an individual human or animal; the period during which someone or something is alive
A period of 24 hours, especially from midnight to midnight; the time between one midnight and the next, or the period of daylight between sunrise and sunset.
The period of darkness in each twenty-four hours; the time from sunset to sunrise when it is dark outside.
the period of time from sunrise until midday; the early part of the day
the period of time at the end of the day, typically from late afternoon until nightfall
a period of ten years
a period of twelve months, corresponding to the time it takes the Earth to complete one orbit around the Sun
A period of roughly four weeks or one of the twelve named divisions of a year, based on the cycle of the moon or the calendar (e.g., January, February).
a period of seven consecutive days, usually starting on Monday or Sunday, used as a unit of time
a unit of time equal to 60 minutes; one of the 24 equal parts of a day
A unit of time equal to sixty seconds or one sixtieth of an hour.
a very short period of time; an instant
The permanent end of all biological functions that sustain a living organism; the cessation of life.

early (adjective): occurring or done before the usual or expected time; near the beginning of a period or event.
early (adverb): before the usual or expected time; sooner than expected.
occurrence of being delayed or arriving after the expected or scheduled time; lateness (e.g., "his late was announced")
the present day; the 24-hour period that includes the current date
a young person; someone who is in the early stage of life or development (youth)
an elderly person; someone who is advanced in age (used as a noun)
The record or study of past events, particularly those concerning human affairs; an account of past actions, developments, or occurrences.
the period of time that has already happened; events and experiences that belong to an earlier time
